            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49178",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blanchon_vincent",
                        "name": "blanchon_vincent",
                        "displayName": "BLANCHON Vincent",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nIn Zend_Controller_Dispatcher_Standard, line 285, there is \"$request->setDispatched(true);\", and this line is AFTER __construct() and init() of the current controller. So, if you want use _forward, you must use preDispatch(), else, the condition \"} while (!$this->_request->isDispatched());\" line 966 in Zend_Controller_Front will be true, and controller name wille the same but not the Action ! It the reason ZF search an action in the current controller ! (number line is used for ZF 1.11.7) ;)\r\n\r\nIt's not a bug ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blanchon_vincent",
                        "name": "blanchon_vincent",
                        "displayName": "BLANCHON Vincent",
                        "active": true
